{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"670k","heading":"Definitions","label":"670k Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch5C/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2011— inserted section catchline.Pub. L. 112–81","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Transfer of FunctionsAtomic Energy Commission abolished and functions transferred by sections 5814 and 5841 of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. See, also, Transfer of Functions notes set out under those sections."],"amendments":["Amendments2011— inserted section catchline.Pub. L. 112–81"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Administrator” means the Administrator of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Chairman” means the Chairman of the Atomic Energy Commission.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any registered motorboat at the option of each State;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any military, fire, emergency, or law enforcement vehicle when used for emergency purposes; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any vehicle the use of which is expressly authorized by the Secretary of the Interior or the Secretary of Agriculture under a permit, lease, license, or contract.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a military reservation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a unit of the National Park System;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F4%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an area within the national wildlife refuge system;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F4%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an Indian reservation; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F4%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an area within an Indian reservation or land held in trust by the United States for an Indian or Indian tribe.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “State agency” means the agency or agencies of a State responsible for the administration of the fish and game laws of the State.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s670k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs670k%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “conservation and rehabilitation programs” means to utilize those methods and procedures which are necessary to protect, conserve, and enhance wildlife, fish, and game resources to the maximum extent practicable on public lands subject to this subchapter consistent with any overall land use and management plans for the lands involved. Such methods and procedures shall include, but shall not be limited to, all activities associated with scientific resources management such as protection, research, census, law enforcement, habitat management, propagation, live trapping and transplantation, and regulated taking in conformance with the provisions of this subchapter. Nothing in this term shall be construed as diminishing the authority or jurisdiction of the States with respect to the management of resident species of fish, wildlife, or game, except as otherwise provided by law.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
